00:01:45.105 --> 00:01:47.007
with my little sister
and my friends.

00:01:47.007 --> 00:01:49.109
That's wonderful.

00:01:49.109 --> 00:01:51.311
Hi. My name's Ash. And this
is my partner, Pikachu.

00:01:51.311 --> 00:01:52.646
[EXCITED]

00:01:52.646 --> 00:01:54.414
Hi. Nice to meet you.

00:01:54.414 --> 00:01:56.950
‐ I'm Serena.
‐ Hi. I'm the little sister.

00:01:56.950 --> 00:01:59.753
My name's Bonnie. Dedenne,
say hi to the nice lady.

00:01:59.753 --> 00:02:02.255
[HAPPY]
Bonnie, Clemont has told me

00:02:02.255 --> 00:02:04.324
how cute and sweet you are.

00:02:04.324 --> 00:02:06.360
It's such a pleasure
to finally meet you.

00:02:06.360 --> 00:02:09.429
And Clemont's told me
a lot about you.

00:02:09.429 --> 00:02:12.566
Always saying how pretty and
nice Professor Eclairisse is.

00:02:12.566 --> 00:02:15.469
I think he really,
really likes you.

00:02:15.469 --> 00:02:18.372
You're a keeper, so please
take care of my brother.

00:02:18.372 --> 00:02:20.407
‐ I'm a keeper?
‐ Right.

00:02:20.407 --> 00:02:22.209
You'd be perfect for him,
'cause you're so smart.

00:02:22.209 --> 00:02:24.444
‐ Ah! Uh, what?
‐ Oh.

00:02:24.444 --> 00:02:27.147
I told you to stop this
a million times.

00:02:27.147 --> 00:02:30.317
Aah! I was just
trying to help you. Come on.

00:02:30.317 --> 00:02:32.486
But I don't need
that kind of help.

00:02:32.486 --> 00:02:33.220
BONNIE
'Come on, Clemont, please?'

00:02:33.220 --> 00:02:34.388
[laughing]

00:02:34.388 --> 00:02:35.322
[AMUSED]

00:02:37.691 --> 00:02:39.192
A school for studying
Electric‐type Pokémon?

00:02:39.192 --> 00:02:41.094
[AMAZED]

00:02:41.094 --> 00:02:43.330
Yeah. It's in
the middle of town.

00:02:43.330 --> 00:02:45.465
See, Clemont
was a student there.

00:02:45.465 --> 00:02:46.967
‐ 'Wow, no joke?'
‐ Nope.

00:02:46.967 --> 00:02:48.702
Look. There it is.

00:02:48.702 --> 00:02:50.537
Would you all like
to come have a look?

00:02:50.537 --> 00:02:52.506
‐ Cool. Is that okay?
‐ Of course, it is.

00:02:55.575 --> 00:02:57.044
[gasps]
[EXCITED]

00:03:04.384 --> 00:03:06.453
'Here at our school,
Trainers travel here'

00:03:06.453 --> 00:03:08.355
'from all over to learn
everything they can'

00:03:08.355 --> 00:03:09.723
'about Electric‐type Pokémon.'

00:03:12.526 --> 00:03:15.295
Our students specialize
in researching the biology

00:03:15.295 --> 00:03:17.764
and behaviors
of Electric‐type Pokémon.

00:03:17.764 --> 00:03:19.533
ECLAIRISSE
'Their studies extend to Pokémon

00:03:19.533 --> 00:03:21.401
of other types as well.'

00:03:21.401 --> 00:03:24.137
'As part of this research,
they learn all about'

00:03:24.137 --> 00:03:27.174
'how people and Pokémon can
and should coexist in harmony.'

00:03:28.141 --> 00:03:31.478
[all gasping]

00:03:31.478 --> 00:03:32.679
ECLAIRISSE
'Many great Trainers have

00:03:32.679 --> 00:03:33.914
gone on to be very successful'

00:03:33.914 --> 00:03:36.216
'after leaving this school.'

00:03:36.216 --> 00:03:39.486
But Clemont is one of the most
notable graduates of all.

00:03:39.486 --> 00:03:41.888
Come on. I think
you're exaggerating a bit.

00:03:41.888 --> 00:03:44.591
No way. You're amazing.

00:03:44.591 --> 00:03:47.394
Yup, you keep coming up
with these totally incredible

00:03:47.394 --> 00:03:48.628
inventions that always
blow up in the end.

00:03:48.628 --> 00:03:51.364
[giggling]

00:03:51.364 --> 00:03:53.433
They call you
the Electric‐type Whiz Kid

00:03:53.433 --> 00:03:55.736
all around Lumiose City,
don't they?

00:03:55.736 --> 00:03:57.504
I know your father
calls you that too.

00:03:57.504 --> 00:04:00.240
Your father?
[gasps]

00:04:00.240 --> 00:04:02.642
SERENA
'That's Meyer, right?'

00:04:02.642 --> 00:04:04.611
You see, it was
my father who told me

00:04:04.611 --> 00:04:06.880
I needed to go to this school.

00:04:06.880 --> 00:04:09.783
"Meet lots of Pokémon Trainers
and make lots of friends.

00:04:09.783 --> 00:04:11.852
Study hard and broaden
your horizons."

00:04:11.852 --> 00:04:14.755
He told me to do that
and off I went.

00:04:14.755 --> 00:04:16.857
So, how did it work out?
Did you make lots of friends?

00:04:16.857 --> 00:04:18.425
[CURIOUS]

00:04:18.425 --> 00:04:20.494
Mm‐hmm, I made friends with

00:04:20.494 --> 00:04:23.096
all kinds of great students
and Pokémon too.

00:04:23.096 --> 00:04:24.631
But all that studying
and research

00:04:24.631 --> 00:04:26.666
was tough, to say the least.

00:04:26.666 --> 00:04:28.535
The curriculum here
is quite rigorous.

00:04:28.535 --> 00:04:30.103
It's a challenge to do the work

00:04:30.103 --> 00:04:32.305
and make it all the way
to graduation.

00:04:32.305 --> 00:04:35.008
Yes, and my graduation research
was particularly tough.

00:04:35.008 --> 00:04:37.577
Graduation research?

00:04:37.577 --> 00:04:40.380
I studied the power
of Electric‐type Pokémon

00:04:40.380 --> 00:04:42.716
and how the power of science
can build the future.

00:04:42.716 --> 00:04:44.951
That was my major focus.

00:04:44.951 --> 00:04:47.554
I recall you did struggle
with that.

00:04:47.554 --> 00:04:50.123
You said you couldn't come up
with any good topics.

00:04:50.123 --> 00:04:52.859
Right, so I used to go for walks
and try to clear my mind.

00:04:52.859 --> 00:04:54.494
That's when I met you‐know‐who.

00:04:58.698 --> 00:05:01.501
Huh? A Shinx.

00:05:01.501 --> 00:05:04.671
[WEAK]
[gasping]

00:05:04.671 --> 00:05:06.473
[grunts]

00:05:06.473 --> 00:05:08.175
Oh, yeah, the Pokémon Center.

00:05:08.175 --> 00:05:09.843
[panting]

00:05:12.979 --> 00:05:14.681
Thanks so much for waiting.

00:05:14.681 --> 00:05:16.950
This Shinx
was completely exhausted

00:05:16.950 --> 00:05:19.419
so it took an exceptional
amount of time to recover.

00:05:19.419 --> 00:05:21.721
[HAPPY]
Ah. What a relief.

00:05:21.721 --> 00:05:23.723
[HAPPY]

00:05:23.723 --> 00:05:26.426
I've seen this more times
than I can count.

00:05:26.426 --> 00:05:29.362
It appears to have something to
do with the local environment.

00:05:29.362 --> 00:05:32.065
If only there were a place
where these Pokémon could easily

00:05:32.065 --> 00:05:34.334
absorb electrical energy..

00:05:34.334 --> 00:05:38.205
A place where they could easily
absorb electrical energy..

00:05:38.205 --> 00:05:41.374
That's it. I've come up
with a great idea, Shinx.

00:05:41.374 --> 00:05:42.843
[laughs]
[CURIOUS]

00:05:44.945 --> 00:05:46.346
I'll collect
the power generated

00:05:46.346 --> 00:05:48.014
by the school's Pokémon

00:05:48.014 --> 00:05:49.649
store it in a battery

00:05:49.649 --> 00:05:51.618
send it by cables
throughout the town

00:05:51.618 --> 00:05:54.054
and make an electricity shower
for Electric types.

00:05:54.054 --> 00:05:56.990
I'll call it
the Clemontic Shower.

00:05:56.990 --> 00:05:59.726
[chuckling]
I can just see it.

00:05:59.726 --> 00:06:02.529
The future is now,
thanks to science.

00:06:02.529 --> 00:06:05.165
[knocking on window]
Huh? Shinx.

00:06:05.165 --> 00:06:06.533
[chuckles]

00:06:09.836 --> 00:06:11.972
Here. See this?

00:06:11.972 --> 00:06:14.207
With my new system,
you'll be able to absorb

00:06:14.207 --> 00:06:16.176
all that electricity
I know you love so much.

00:06:16.176 --> 00:06:18.445
[HAPPY]

00:06:18.445 --> 00:06:21.314
I wanna make a town where
Electric‐types can live happily.

00:06:21.314 --> 00:06:24.050
No, a world where
all Pokémon can live happily.

00:06:24.050 --> 00:06:26.519
That would be
my dream come true.

00:06:26.519 --> 00:06:29.422
Shinx, you'd live there,
now, wouldn't you?

00:06:29.422 --> 00:06:30.891
Huh?
[EXCITED]

00:06:34.628 --> 00:06:38.031
That's how I completed my
graduate research project.

00:06:38.031 --> 00:06:40.867
The electrical transmission
system that Clemont invented

00:06:40.867 --> 00:06:43.536
was well received
not only by the school

00:06:43.536 --> 00:06:45.305
but by the entire town's
population as well.

00:06:48.208 --> 00:06:49.809
What a great story.

00:06:49.809 --> 00:06:51.478
That's the very first time

00:06:51.478 --> 00:06:52.512
I heard Clemont
talk about Shinx.

00:06:52.512 --> 00:06:54.180
[AGREEMENT]

00:06:56.383 --> 00:06:59.152
Fascinating.

00:06:59.152 --> 00:07:01.655
So, this town has an ample
supply of electrical energy.

00:07:01.655 --> 00:07:03.623
In that case, let's steal

00:07:03.623 --> 00:07:06.192
every last bit of that energy
for ourselves.

00:07:06.192 --> 00:07:09.296
